1964;;The Brass Bottle;;American;;Harry Keller;;Tony Randall, Burl Ives, Barbara Eden;;fantasy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Brass_Bottle_(1964_film);;Architect Harold Ventimore (Tony Randall) buys a large antique container that turns out to imprison a djinn named Fakrash (Burl Ives), whom Harold inadvertently sets free. Fakrash is effusively grateful for his release, and persistently tries to do favors for Harold to show his gratitude. However he has been in the brass bottle for a long time, and Fakrashâ€™s unfamiliarity with the modern world causes all sorts of problems when he tries to please his rescuer. Harold ends up in a great deal of trouble, including with his girlfriend, Sylvia Kenton (Barbara Eden).